HEADWORD: Respectful
<hw>Re*spect"ful</hw> <pr>(-f?l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Marked or
characterized by respect; <as>as, <ex>respectful</ex>
deportment</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With humble joy and with <qex>respectful</qex> fear.</q>
<rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Re*spect"ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Re*spect"ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Respecting</ent>⟦br⟧
